name: mapreduce.task.timeout
description:
The number of milliseconds before a task will be
  terminated if it neither reads an input, writes an output, nor
  updates its status string.  A value of 0 disables the timeout.

name: fs.s3a.connection.maximum
description:
Controls the maximum number of simultaneous connections to S3.
    This must be bigger than the value of fs.s3a.threads.max so as to stop
    threads being blocked waiting for new HTTPS connections.
    Why not equal? The AWS SDK transfer manager also uses these connections.

name: dfs.namenode.available-space-rack-fault-tolerant-block-placement-policy.balanced-space-tolerance
description:
Only used when the dfs.block.replicator.classname is set to
    org.apache.hadoop.hdfs.server.blockmanagement.AvailableSpaceRackFaultTolerantBlockPlacementPolicy.
    Special value between 0 and 20, inclusive. if the value is set beyond the scope,
    this value will be set as 5 by default, Increases tolerance of
    placing blocks on Datanodes with similar disk space used.

name: dfs.namenode.delegation.token.renew-interval
description: The renewal interval for delegation token in milliseconds.

name: dfs.qjournal.get-journal-state.timeout.ms
description:
Timeout in milliseconds when calling getJournalState().
    JournalNodes.

name: nfs.wtmax
description:
This is the maximum size in bytes of a WRITE request
    supported by the NFS gateway. If you change this, make sure you
    also update the nfs mount's wsize(add wsize= # of bytes to the 
    mount directive).

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client-am.ipc.max-retries
description:
The number of client retries to the AM - before reconnecting
    to the RM to fetch Application Status.
    In other words, it is the ipc.client.connect.max.retries to be used during
    reconnecting to the RM and fetching Application Status.

name: dfs.namenode.reencrypt.edek.threads
description:
Maximum number of re-encrypt threads to contact the KMS
    and re-encrypt the edeks.

name: ipc.client.kill.max
description: Defines the maximum number of clients to disconnect in one go.
